 On Thursday the church also hosted a Women’s Tea in celebration of Women’s Day. A Gatsby Murder Mystery themed gala dinner will be hosted on Friday while the men and children can look forward to a pampering on Saturday with a breakfast for the dads and a Boeresport Day for the youngsters. The celebrations will culminate in a service on Sunday by the church’s first locally ordained female Reverend, Reverend Carol Lubbe. Everyone is welcome to join the congregation for the celebrations. For more information contact the church office on 013 282 7380.    Dullstroom farm attack trial postponed Middelburg weekly weather forecast  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email.